events.description: Release of the Swedish inflation rate for January 2026.

facts.fact_text: The annual inflation rate in Sweden rose to 0.4% in January 2026.

evidences.evidence_text: The annual inflation rate in Sweden rose to 0.4% in January 2026

facts.fact_text: The annual inflation rate in Sweden was 0.3% in the previous month.
Market expectations for the annual inflation rate were 0.6%.

evidences.evidence_text: The latest figure came in below market expectations of 0.6%

facts.fact_text: The annual inflation rate was the highest since October.

evidences.evidence_text: but marked the highest reading since October.

facts.fact_text: Consumer prices edged up by 0.1% in January on a monthly basis.

evidences.evidence_text: On a monthly basis, consumer prices edged up by 0.1% in January

facts.fact_text: Consumer prices showed no growth in December on a monthly basis.

evidences.evidence_text: after showing no growth in December.

facts.fact_text: The CPIF increased by 2% year-on-year in January.

evidences.evidence_text: Meanwhile, the CPI with a fixed interest rate (CPIF), the Riskbank’s target measure, increased by 2% year-on-year in January

facts.fact_text: The CPIF increase of 2% in January was slightly less than the 2.1% rise in the previous month.

evidences.evidence_text: slightly easing from a 2.1% rise in the previous month

facts.fact_text: Market forecasts for the CPIF increase were 2.1%.

evidences.evidence_text: and falling short of market forecasts of a 2.1% gain.
